<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The rules concerning the secret archives, distinct from the general archives and the historical archives, are explained in John P. Beal, James A. Coriden, Thomas J. Green, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=X5rcnhLnRYMC&amp;dq=%22secret+archives%22+%22canon+law%22&amp;pg=PA643"><i>A New Commentary on the Code of Canon Law</i></a>, 642-644.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Servanda diligenter in archivio secreto curiae pro norma interna. Non publicanda nec ullis commentariis augenda" (heading of the Instruction).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.richardsipe.com/Doyle/2008/2008-10-03-Commentary%20on%201922%20and%201962%20documents.pdf">Thomas Doyle, <i>The 1922 Instruction and the 1962 Instruction </i>Crimen sollicitationis<i> </i></a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110715183919/http://www.richardsipe.com/Doyle/2008/2008-10-03-Commentary%20on%201922%20and%201962%20documents.pdf">Archived</a> 15 July 2011 at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a>, section 2</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">An English translation of the papal document and of the new norms can be consulted at <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.bishop-accountability.org/resources/resource-files/churchdocs/SacramentorumAndNormaeEnglish.htm">this site</a> and a guide to procedures regarding accusations of clerical sexual abuse is available on the Holy See <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.vatican.va/resources/resources_guide-CDF-procedures_en.html">website.</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110903143810/https://www.vatican.va/resources/resources_guide-CDF-procedures_en.html">Archived</a> 3 September 2011 at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.vatican.va/roman_curia/congregations/cfaith/documents/rc_con_cfaith_doc_20010518_epistula_graviora%20delicta_lt.html#_ftnref3"><i>De delictis gravioribus</i></a>, second paragraph</span>
